---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Australian Home Collective"
  description="Australian Home Collective creates practical home guides that help Australian households measure, check and plan before buying storage, organisation and household products."
>
  <header class="page-intro">
    <div class="narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>About Australian Home Collective</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Australian Home Collective is a practical home guide site for Australian households.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>
  <section class="content narrow">
    <p>
      The site focuses on the decisions people make before buying storage, organisation
      and household products. Instead of starting with a product list, our guides usually
      start with the space, the problem and the checks that matter before money is spent.
    </p>
    <p>
      Many home purchases go wrong for simple reasons: the item does not fit, it does not
      suit a rental, it is hard to clean, it blocks daily use, or it solves the wrong problem.
    </p>
    <p>
      Australian Home Collective is built around practical pre-buying guidance.
    </p>

    <h2>What the site covers</h2>
    <p>
      Australian Home Collective focuses on everyday household areas such as:
    </p>
    <ul class="feature-list">
      <li>kitchen storage</li>
      <li>laundry storage</li>
      <li>pantry organisation</li>
      <li>garage storage</li>
      <li>bathroom storage</li>
      <li>pet-related home products</li>
      <li>nursery and family home basics</li>
      <li>small-space and renter-friendly storage</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The site is designed for people who want clear, useful information before buying.
    </p>

    <h2>Our approach</h2>
    <p>
      Our guides usually focus on:
    </p>
    <ul class="feature-list">
      <li>what to measure</li>
      <li>what to check</li>
      <li>common mistakes to avoid</li>
      <li>renter-friendly considerations</li>
      <li>cleaning and maintenance issues</li>
      <li>household suitability</li>
      <li>when not to buy anything yet</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      This approach is deliberate. A product can look useful online but still be wrong for
      a particular home. Measurements, layout, daily habits and maintenance often matter
      more than a product photo.
    </p>

    <h2>What we do not claim</h2>
    <p>
      Australian Home Collective does not claim to personally test every product mentioned
      unless an article clearly says so.
    </p>
    <p>
      The site does not invent product testing, fake reviews, fake personal experience,
      fake prices or unsupported claims. Where a guide discusses a product type, it is
      usually explaining what to check before buying that kind of product.
    </p>

    <h2>Why this matters</h2>
    <p>
      A useful home guide should help readers avoid poor purchases, not push them into
      buying more.
    </p>
    <p>
      Sometimes the best answer is to measure first. Sometimes it is to clear duplicates.
      Sometimes it is to choose a removable option for a rental. Sometimes it is not to buy
      anything yet.
    </p>
    <p>
      Australian Home Collective aims to make those decisions easier.
    </p>

    <p>
      You can also read more about <a href="/editorial-standards/">our editorial standards</a>
      {" "}and <a href="/our-approach/">our before-you-buy approach</a>.
    </p>
    <p class="small">
      Images and written content on this site are owned by Australian Home Collective unless
      otherwise stated.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
